# Implementation Plan - Reports Filtering & Monitor Enhancements

## Goal Description
Enhance the Reports tab with interactive date filtering (specifically for dates after Dec 25, 2025) and improve the Anomaly Monitor with a "Copy Subject" feature.

## User Review Required
None specifically, but note that date filtering relies on string parsing of "MM/DD/YYYY".

## Proposed Changes

### Reports Tab (Date Filtering)
#### [MODIFY] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Projects/Interview%20Task%20Status%20Checker/web/app/api/reports/route.ts)
- Add query parameter handling for `startDate` and `endDate`.
- Add filtering logic to parse `Date of Interview` string and compare against the range.
- **Logic:** `new Date(taskDateTime) >= new Date(startDate)`

#### [MODIFY] [ReportsFeed.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Projects/Interview%20Task%20Status%20Checker/web/components/ReportsFeed.tsx)
- Add State for `startDate` and `endDate`.
- Add Date Input UI to the header.
- Pass these params to [fetchReport](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Projects/Interview%20Task%20Status%20Checker/web/components/ReportsFeed.tsx#42-55).

### Anomaly Monitor (Copy Subject)
#### [MODIFY] [TaskFeed.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Projects/Interview%20Task%20Status%20Checker/web/components/TaskFeed.tsx)
- Update [ITask](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Projects/Interview%20Task%20Status%20Checker/web/components/TaskFeed.tsx#18-28) interface to include `Subject` (optional).
- Add a hover button next to Candidate Name that copies `task.Subject || "No Subject"` to clipboard.
- Use `navigator.clipboard.writeText`.

